  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large wok or frying pan over medium-high heat.",
    "Add onion, garlic, and ginger and saut\u00056 until the onion is translucent.",
    "Add Toor Dal, paprika, cumin, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper. Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.",
    "Add Fry Grind Rice Khao Khua and cook for 1-2 minutes, stirring constantly.",
    "Add heavy cream and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer for 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "The sauce should be thick and molten. Serve hot, garnished with chopped cilantro if desired."
